**Analysis of Administrative Unit Change for "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ"**

Okay, so the user is looking for the updated administrative unit for "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ, Huyện Quỳnh Phụ, Tỉnh Thái Bình". My process here is fairly straightforward, but it requires careful attention to detail and cross-referencing.

First, I identified "Tỉnh Thái Bình" as the old province. Checking the relevant resolutions (specifically, those related to implementing Resolution 60-NQ/TW) led me to the conclusion that "Tỉnh Thái Bình" was *merged* with "Tỉnh Hưng Yên" to form a single entity, "Tỉnh Hưng Yên". This is crucial, as it dictates the scope of my search going forward.

Next, the focus shifted to the ward itself, "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ".  I knew I had to search within the context of the *new* province, "Tỉnh Hưng Yên". I diligently reviewed available resolutions, meticulously scanning for any mention of "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ". Resolution `1666/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của tỉnh Hưng Yên` caught my eye.

Specifically, line 62 of the resolution was the key: "Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của thị trấn Quỳnh Côi và các xã Quỳnh Hải, Quỳnh Hội, Quỳnh Hồng, Quỳnh Mỹ, Quỳnh Hưng thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Quỳnh Phụ**."  This directly addresses "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ" and indicates its merger into the new unit, "Xã Quỳnh Phụ".  Furthermore, this resolution falls under the purview of "Tỉnh Hưng Yên", which solidified my confidence in the finding, since the merging of the two provinces happened already.  The mention of "huyện Quỳnh Phụ" (old district in Thái Bình) within the resolution further solidifies this association.

To confirm this, I cross-referenced this information against the "New wards" list, verifying that "Xã Quỳnh Phụ" is indeed listed and correctly associated with "Tỉnh Hưng Yên" ( `{"ward_code":"12472","ward_name":"Xã Quỳnh Phụ","province_name":"Tỉnh Hưng Yên"}` ). This final confirmation clinched my finding.

To be extra sure, I also quickly scanned other relevant resolutions (Hà Nội, Bắc Ninh, Nghệ An) to verify that there are no conflicting mentions or alternative matches for "Xã Quỳnh Mỹ".
